    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To examine the impact of a structured physical activity program focused on bone strength in
      elementary school children in the framework of their physical education classes on:

        1. Bone strength of children participating in the activity.

        2. Physical variables and psycho-motor capabilities: vertical jumping strength, horizontal
           jumping strength, static balance, dynamic balance and coordination.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
